label.value: mesenchymal cell differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a mesenchymal cell of the salivary gland. A mesenchymal cell is a loosely associated cell that is part of the connective tissue in an organism. Mesenchymal cells give rise to more mature connective tissue cell types.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in salivary gland morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of branching morphogenesis in the salivary gland epithelium.

label.value: regulation of phospholipid catabolic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of phospholipid catabolism, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of phospholipids, any lipid containing phosphoric acid as a mono- or diester.

label.value: positive regulation of phospholipid catabolic process

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of phospholipid catabolism, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of phospholipids, any lipid containing phosphoric acid as a mono- or diester.

label.value: acinar cell differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize an acinar cell of the salivary gland. Acinar cells are protein-secreting cells in the gland.

label.value: neuron differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the neurons of the salivary gland.

label.value: cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of the embryonic placenta.

label.value: spongiotrophoblast differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell of the ectoplacental cone acquires specialized features of a spongiotrophoblast of the placenta. A spongiotrophoblast cell is a basophilic cell.

label.value: labyrinthine layer development

value.value: The process in which the labyrinthine layer of the placenta progresses, from its formation to its mature state.

label.value: spongiotrophoblast layer development

value.value: The process in which the spongiotrophoblast layer of the placenta progresses from its formation to its mature state.

label.value: labyrinthine layer morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the labyrinthine layer of the placenta is generated and organized.

label.value: labyrinthine layer formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the labyrinthine layer of the placenta.

label.value: labyrinthine layer blood vessel development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a blood vessel of the labyrinthine layer of the placenta over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The embryonic vessels grow through the layer to come in close contact with the maternal blood supply.

label.value: chorion development

value.value: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a chorion from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the structure and ends with the mature structure. The chorion is an extraembryonic membrane.

label.value: chorionic trophoblast cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells of the ectoplacental cone acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize chorionic trophoblasts. These cells will migrate towards the spongiotrophoblast layer and give rise to syncytiotrophoblasts of the labyrinthine layer.

label.value: chorionic trophoblast cell development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the chorionic trophoblast over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cell development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to a specific fate.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of the population in the embryonic placenta.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development.

label.value: prostate gland growth

value.value: The increase in size or mass of the prostate gland where the increase in size or mass has the specific outcome of the progression of the gland, from its formation to its mature state.

label.value: prostate gland morphogenetic growth

value.value: The differential increase in size or mass of the prostate gland that contributes to the gland attaining its form.

label.value: epithelial-mesenchymal signaling involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that results in the transfer of information from an epithelial cell to a mesenchymal cell where it is interpreted and contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: mesenchymal-epithelial cell signaling involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from a mesenchymal cell to an epithelial cell where it is received and interpreted contributing to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: prostate gland epithelium morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of epithelia of the prostate gland are generated and organized. An epithelium consists of closely packed cells arranged in one or more layers, that covers the outer surfaces of the body or lines any internal cavity or tube.

label.value: prostate gland stromal morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the prostate gland stroma is generated and organized. The prostate gland stroma is made up of the mesenchymal or fibroblast cells of the prostate gland.

label.value: epithelial cell differentiation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an epithelial cell of the prostate gland.

label.value: epithelial cell maturation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: The developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an epithelial cell of the prostate gland to attain its fully functional state. An epithelial cell is a cell usually found in a two-dimensional sheet with a free surface.

label.value: mammary gland alveolus development

value.value: The progression of the mammary gland alveolus over time, from its formation to its mature state. The mammary gland alveolus is a sac-like structure that is found in the mature gland.

label.value: regulation of response to cytokine stimulus

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of a response to cytokine stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of response to cytokine stimulus

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of a response to cytokine stimulus.

label.value: negative regulation of response to cytokine stimulus

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of a response to cytokine stimulus.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in mammary gland duct morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of branching involved in mammary gland duct morphogenesis.

label.value: mammary duct terminal end bud growth

value.value: The morphogenetic growth of the large, club-shaped terminal end of a mammary gland duct during prepubertal growth and during puberty.

label.value: cell-cell signaling involved in mammary gland development

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another and contributes to the progression of the mammary gland, from its initial state to the mature structure.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: positive regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: negative regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of mesenchymal cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: regulation of mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time. A mesenchymal cell is a cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in tissue homeostasis

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation resulting in the maintenance of a steady-state number of cells within a tissue.

label.value: regulation of apoptosis involved in tissue homeostasis

value.value: Any process that modulates the occurrence or rate of cell death by apoptosis that results in the maintenance of the steady-state number of cells within a tissue.

label.value: regulation of cell differentiation involved in tissue homeostasis

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell differentiation that contributes to the maintenance of a steady state of a cell type within a tissue.

label.value: ectodermal placode formation

value.value: The developmental process in which an ectodermal placode forms. An ectodermal placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that is the primordium of many structures derived from the ectoderm.

label.value: hair follicle placode formation

value.value: The developmental process in which a hair placode forms. An hair follicle placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that will give rise to the hair follicle bud.

label.value: tooth placode formation

value.value: The developmental process in which the tooth placode forms. A tooth placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that will give rise to the tooth bud.

label.value: sebaceous gland placode formation

value.value: The developmental process in which a sebaceous gland placode forms. A sebaceous gland placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that will give rise to the sebaceous gland bud.

label.value: sweat gland development

value.value: The progression of the sweat gland over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Sweat glands secrete an aqueous solution that is used in thermoregulation.

label.value: sweat gland placode formation

value.value: The developmental process in which the sweat gland placode forms. An sweat gland placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that will give rise to the sweat gland bud.

label.value: cell fate commitment involved in formation of primary germ layer

value.value: The commitment of cells to specific cell fates of the endoderm, ectoderm, or mesoderm as a part of gastrulation.

label.value: regulation of cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of cell differentiation that contributes to the progression of the placenta over time, from its initial condition to its mature state.
